{{Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic| name=Scourgify| type=[[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic#Spells|Spell]] (Charm)| features=Cleans up foreign material| appearance=[[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Books/Order of the Phoenix/Chapter 3|''Harry Potter and the Order of the Phoenix'']]}}
== Overview ==
'''''Scourgify''''' is one of the cleaning charms, used to clean foreign material off surfaces.
== Extended Description ==
{{Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Beginner Spoiler}}
In [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Books/Order of the Phoenix|''Harry Potter and the Order of the Phoenix'']], we see it a couple of times; [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Nymphadora Tonks|Tonks]] uses it with limited results to clean [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Hedwig|Hedwig]]'s cage (she admits that she's not very good at that); and [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Ginny Weasley|Ginny]] uses it to clean up the Stinksap that [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Neville Longbottom|Neville]]'s [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic/Mimbulus Mimbletonia|Mimbulus Mimbletonia]] has sprayed around the compartment of the Hogwarts Express. It is also used to "wash out" [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Severus Snape|a young Snape]]'s mouth in ''Harry Potter and the Order of the Phoenix''.
== Analysis ==
Scourgify seems to be limited to surfaces; it cannot restore spilled liquids to a container, only eliminating them. It also is not used to remove foreign matter from a container; [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic/Evanesco|Evanesco]] is used for that – which may be why Tonks' attempt to clean Hedwig's cage, a container, does not succeed. There is also a charm [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic/Tergeo|Tergeo]] that seems to be used for almost the same purpose.
